history.text: Hello!

Hi there, 
Wow, LaLa Land is a musical, I didn't know that.
did you?
Yes, I enjoyed that the actors did all their own singing and dancing!
Do you like jazz music?
Do you think it matters that the movie uses white actors but relies heavily on art forms traditionally associated with black culture?
How neat, seems like a lot of work.
oh sorry that didn't answer your question, that was a response to your previous remark.
What do you think of it being shot in Cinemascope?
thats a good question & Im not sure. I think jazz speaks to all kinds of people & those who love it know its roots.
I like the use of color thought the movie.
It's very brightly colored, that's true.  Do you think that adds to the mood of the film?
Did you enjoy the scene where the two lead actors first meet?
in the restaurant, i felt bad for him when he got fired.
it was christmas.
Agreed.  I liked how that scene showed how serious he felt about music.
yes, you are right. did you think it was funny when she ran into at the party?
Yes! I liked that he was in a cover band - it showed how difficult it is to make a living as a musician.
What did you think of his career decision to play in a band he didn't love?
Seems like tough decision, i thought the movie conveyed that well.
What did you think of her reaction at watching him onstage?.
Yes. Both actors struggled.  I like that they encouraged each other - like when he encouraged her to write a play
It was thoughtful -- it showed she knew him well and wanted him to be happy
your very insightful
Do you think they should have broken up when he missed her play?
I'm not sure.  I think ultimately it was good for them.
It would have been disingenuous for her to act against how she felt -- both of them were such emotional people who made decisions based on strong emotions
What did you think of her decision to go home?
true, i thought it was realistic for her to go home. But i hate that she had given up.
you?

I guess Nevada isn't
 so far away
I thought it was a nice illustration of what it feels like to lose hope
But also, because it was such a colorful, musical, film I felt confident that it would not end that way for her -- that she would go back and try again
Did you feel that way?
Yes, I did. At that point i was hoping it didn't end like that.
I thought it was very realistic for her play to flop, also.
Yes, but I felt so bad for her.

understandable but, 
if it would have been as success, it wold have been to easy.
What did you think when she overheard people saying unkind things?
That it was rude but typical and a little sad because you felt she put a lot of work into it.
Yes
She tried so hard
she did
I did enjoy the audition scenes she did, that was funny.
I agree!
I liked seeing her against other versions of her type.
Yes Emma Stone has a lot of range
Ryan too, I didn't know he could sing & dance.
